Problem #7 (3 points)

Quinn accelerates at a rate of $2.45 \frac{\mathrm{blark}}{\mathrm{zoomer}^{2}}$.

Extra information

$1.00 \mathrm{blark}$ $=$ $0.592 \mathrm{yd}$

$1.00 \mathrm{yd}$ $=$ $0.914 \mathrm{m}$

$1.00 \mathrm{zoomer}$ $=$ $1.20 \mathrm{h}$

$1.00 \mathrm{h}$ $=$ $3.60e+03 \mathrm{s}$

Question #1 (3 points)

Determine Quinn's acceleration in $\frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}^{2}}$.

$ 2.45 \frac{\mathrm{blark}}{\mathrm{zoomer}^{2}} \cdot \frac{0.592 \mathrm{yd}}{1.00 \mathrm{blark}} \cdot \frac{0.914 \mathrm{m}}{1.00 \mathrm{yd}} \cdot \frac{1.00 \mathrm{zoomer}}{1.20 \mathrm{h}} \cdot \frac{1.00 \mathrm{zoomer}}{1.20 \mathrm{h}} \cdot \frac{1.00 \mathrm{h}}{3.60e+03 \mathrm{s}} \cdot \frac{1.00 \mathrm{h}}{3.60e+03 \mathrm{s}}= 7.10e-08 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}^{2}}$

Problem #8 (6 points)

Alvin Kamara has a mass of $97.1 \mathrm{kg}$ and ran $36.6 \mathrm{m}$, accelerating to a speed of $8.02 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}}$.

Question #1 (3 points)

Determine Alvin's acceleration.

$v_{x}^2 = v_{0_x}^2 + 2 a \Delta x$

where $v_{0_x} = 0$

$a=\frac{v_x^2}{2\Delta x}$; $a=\frac{(8.02 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}})^2}{2 \cdot 36.6 \mathrm{m}}$

$a=$ $0.879 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}^{2}}$

Question #2 (3 points)

Determine Alvin's time in the $36.6 \mathrm{m}$ dash.

$v_x = v_{0_x} + a t$

where $v_{0_x} = 0$

$t = \frac{v_x}{a}$; $t = \frac{8.02 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}}}{0.879 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}^{2}}}$

$t=$ $9.13 \mathrm{s}$

Problem #9 (6 points)

A person is on top of a building and drops a stone. The stone hits the ground $3.50 \mathrm{s}$ later.

Question #1 (3 points)

Determine the velocity of the stone when it hits the ground.

$v_y=v_0+at$

where $v_0=0$; $a=-g=$ $-9.81 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}^{2}}$; $v_y=$ $-9.81 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}^{2}}$ $3.50 \mathrm{s}$

$v_y=$ $-34.3 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}}$ .

Question #2 (3 points)

Determine the height of the building.

$y=y_0+v_{0_y}t+\frac12at^2$

where $y_0=0$; $v_{0_y}=0$; $a=$ $-9.81 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}^{2}}$

$y=$ $-60.1 \mathrm{m}$

$h=|y|=$ $60.1 \mathrm{m}$.

Pikachu uses Thunderbolt, discharging a current of $15.0 \mathrm{A}$ through a $20.0 \mathrm{Ω}$ resistor. How much electrical power does Pikachu generate? Use the formula $P = I^2 R$. $P=$ $4.50e+03 \mathrm{W}$

Problem #11 (12 points)

Joseph Fourier tosses a stone of mass of $0.430 \mathrm{kg}$ with a speed of $26.8 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}}$ at an angle of $18.3 ^\circ$ degrees above the horizontal from a height of $1.20 \mathrm{m}$ towards a wall that is $30.5 \mathrm{m}$ away.

Question #1 (3 points)

Create and draw a well labeled diagram of the situation. Be sure to include all known and unknown quantities.

Question #2 (3 points)

Resolve the initial velocity into $x$ and $y$ components.

$v_{0_x} = v_0 \cos(\theta_i)$; $v_{0_y} = v_0 \sin(\theta_i)$

$v_{0_x} = 26.8 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}} \cos(18.3 ^\circ)$; $v_{0_y} = 26.8 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}} \sin(18.3 ^\circ)$

$v_{0_x} = 25.4 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}}$; $v_{0_y} = 8.41 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}}$

Question #3 (3 points)

Determine the time ($t$) taken for the stone to hit the wall.

$x_f = x_0 + v_{0_x} t$

where $x_0 = 0$; $v_{0_x} = 25.4 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}}$

$t = \frac{x_f}{v_{0_x}}$; $t = \frac{30.5 \mathrm{m}}{25.4 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}}}$

$t = 1.20 \mathrm{s}$

Question #4 (3 points)

Determine the height of the stone when it hits the wall.

$y = y_0 + v_{0_y} t + \frac{1}{2} a t^2$

where $y_0 = 1.20 \mathrm{m}$; $v_{0_y} = 8.41 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}}$; $a = -g = -9.81 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}^{2}}$; $t=1.20 \mathrm{s}$

$y = 1.20 \mathrm{m} + 8.41 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}} \cdot 1.20 \mathrm{s} + \frac{1}{2} (-9.81 \frac{\mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}^{2}}) (3.50 \mathrm{s})^2$

$y = 4.24 \mathrm{m}$
